  "body": "RPC logging does not include an IP address of the requester, and it would be really useful if it did.  Even at debug level, it does not mention the IP address of requestors.\r\n\r\nInstead of logging the RPC request ID, log the IP address of the remote connection - this is indicated by the network stack, or the x-forwarded-for HTTP header introduced by servers such as nginx that commonly do SSL termination.\r\n\r\nThe issue is that I plan to build in automated defence against network attacks over RPC. Collect and identify the probe fingerprint, drop the requesting IP.   \r\n\r\n",
